## About SYSUM

### Brand Story
Born from a love of the rugged British wilderness, SYSUM inspires exploration and connection with the wild. We create premium technical trail running apparel designed for long-distance adventures and outdoor exploration.

### Brand Values
- Focus: Trail running, ultra-distance events, British wilderness exploration
- Philosophy: Durability, sustainability, functional design
- Manufacturing: Ethically produced in Portugal
- Materials: Focus on durability (Cordura®), recycled components where possible
- Ethos: Connection with nature, exploration, performance over fashion
- Target Customer: Serious trail runners, ultra-distance athletes, wilderness adventurers
- Price Positioning: Premium technical gear, accessible luxury performance wear

### Manufacturing & Sustainability
- Production Location: Portugal (ethical manufacturing)
- Fabric Sourcing: France (low carbon impact energy)
- Shipping to Warehouse: Land or boat only (no air freight)
- Packaging: FSC-certified renewable wood fibers, recycled paper materials, 100% plastic-free, 100% recyclable
- Philosophy: Durability prioritized over recyclability for longevity
- Certifications: Responsible Wool Standard where applicable

